+def _pair_toi_box_scale(start_a, prop_a, start_b, prop_b, rho_a, rho_b, head_a, reach_a, head_b, reach_b):
+    """[v2 Stage C] Smallest tick-fraction s in (0,1] at which cell A (centre gliding start_a->prop_a,
+    throttled by rho_a) and cell B (start_b->prop_b, rho_b) first bring their OBB engagement surfaces
+    into contact (obb_front_reach_overlap), or None if the boxes never touch across this tick's
+    throttled motion. Headings/reach are fixed over the tick (motion stays Euclidean -- only the centre
+    translates); each box is the unit square grown by reach_front on its front face. Deterministic (no
+    RNG, no set iteration). Returns 0.0 if already touching at s=0 (a pre-existing contact -- normally
+    caught by halted_cells; defensive freeze here). See _TOI_BOX_SCAN/_TOI_BOX_BISECT for precision."""
+    # [v2 Stage C perf reconcile, ED-MB-0011] Precompute the constant per-tick geometry ONCE, not
+    # ~30x inside the bisection. Over a single tick the headings, reach and box extents are FIXED and
+    # only the CENTRES translate linearly in s, so each corner's OFFSET from its centre is constant.
+    # Profiling showed the old _touch rebuilt both CellBoxes (cellbox_from + _cellbox_corners, the trig/
+    # corner reconstruction) on every one of ~30 iterations per pair -- ~4.5s of a 9s battle. Caching
+    # the axes + corner-offset vectors and lerping only the centre drops that to plain adds. Same SAT
+    # algorithm, same result (verified by diff against the pre-cache bisection as an oracle).
+    _ba0 = cellbox_from(0.0, 0.0, head_a, w=1.0, d=1.0, reach_front=reach_a)  # centre at origin
+    _bb0 = cellbox_from(0.0, 0.0, head_b, w=1.0, d=1.0, reach_front=reach_b)
+    axes_a = _cellbox_axes(_ba0)
+    axes_b = _cellbox_axes(_bb0)
+    # offsets for the two directional configs of obb_front_reach_overlap:
